## PORTFOLIO SUMMARY

This portfolio balances growth and value across three distinct themes: (1) **AI Infrastructure Beneficiaries** (MRVL) capturing the semiconductor boom from data center capex; (2) **Post-Pandemic Cyclical Recovery** (CCL) leveraging strong consumer spending and booking momentum; and (3) **Digital/Consumer Transition** (ROKU, SFM, HIMS) benefiting from streaming adoption, organic food demand, and telehealth penetration. Sector diversification spans semiconductors, consumer discretionary, consumer staples, media/technology, and healthcare. The portfolio tilts toward high-conviction, high-growth positions (MRVL, CCL) with supporting medium-conviction plays in emerging digital consumer trends. Overall risk profile is moderate with catalysts driven by macro tailwinds (AI spending, consumer confidence) and company-specific execution (margin expansion, subscriber growth). All five companies are rated A or B for investment grade and demonstrate clear earnings visibility, favorable valuations relative to growth, and strong analyst support.